snippet.textDisplay: Any possibility you could suspend charging income tax for a few months so that people who are working round the clock to support all Canadians aren't paying tax as if they were wealthy bureaucrats? They are out there risking their lives regardless of the social-distancing measures. It would also help those who have their hours reduced due to loss of activity in their sector of the supply chain, but are still considered essential workers. I supplied a manufacturer with parts to make wheelchairs and stretchers the other day but that doesn't mean I have anywhere near the amount of work to do since I also supply parts to the entertainment/lighting and stage sector which has shut down completely.
